   =20
      Chats
   =20
 =20
 This really shows signs of being the next big banking scandal, and yet it =
is so dumb:HSBC Holdings Plc fired a trader in London after scrutinizing th=
e personal mobile phones of some staff, in a sign of increased pressure on =
banks to closely monitor business communications.=C2=A0Earlier this year, t=
he lender=E2=80=99s UK-based compliance team pushed some traders and banker=
s to hand over their phones so they could examine business messages on plat=
forms such as WhatsApp, according to people familiar with the matter. As re=
sult of the review a trader on the foreign exchange desk was dismissed, the=
 people added, declining to identify the individual.=C2=A0The bank=E2=80=99=
s review of the trader=E2=80=99s phone found communications it deemed probl=
ematic, including a chat several years ago with a broker who had bought the=
 banker tickets for a sporting event, the people said, asking not to be nam=
ed discussing a private probe.=C2=A0Banks have tried to enhance surveillanc=
e on the fear that flexible working has exacerbated the use of unapproved c=
ommunications channels. Regulators have been pushing firms to make sure the=
ir employees don=E2=80=99t improperly use personal mobiles for conversation=
s with clients.We talked about another one, at Credit Suisse Group AG,  yes=
terday, and JPMorgan Chase & Co. paid $200 million of fines for this stuff =
last year.=C2=A0Every bank is going to fire a bunch of people and pay=C2=A0=
nine-digit fines over, like, =E2=80=9Cyou used WhatsApp to invite a client =
to play golf.=E2=80=9D There will be little or no evidence that anyone did =
substantive crimes =E2=80=94=C2=A0no one will be caught bribing government =
officials or colluding on prices or sharing nonpublic information over What=
sApp =E2=80=94=C2=A0but the record-keeping failures will get everyone.I gue=
ss that=E2=80=99s good? When the biggest banking scandal is this harmless a=
nd boring, maybe that means=C2=A0the banks have cleaned up their act so muc=
h that there are no more real problems to address. Or maybe there are real =
problems and regulators are distracted by the chat thing because it is so w=
idespread and easy to understand. Or maybe there are real problems and we d=
on=E2=80=99t know about them because all the bad stuff happens in the Whats=
App chats.
