in loan to Celsius, backed by Bitcoin. Tether <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/28067458.269601/aHR0cHM6Ly90ZXRoZXIudG8vZW4vdGV=
0aGVyLWNvbmRlbW5zLWZhbHNlLXJ1bW91cnMtYWJvdXQtaXRzLWNvbW1lcmNpYWwtcGFwZXItaG=
9sZGluZ3Mv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfdad9b8d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">put out a blog post</=
a> today to reassure the market, and it is not entirely reassuring:</p><blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tether can report that its current por=
tfolio of commercial paper has since been further reduced to 11 billion (fr=
om 20 billion at the end of Q1 2022), and will be 8.4 billion by end June 2=
022. This will gradually decrease to zero without any incurrences of losses=
. All commercial papers are expiring and will be rolled into US Treasuries =
with a short maturity.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=
=9CThis will gradually decrease to zero without any incurrences of losses=
=E2=80=9D is a weird thing to say. If any of your commercial paper defaults=
 before it matures, you will incur losses. Certainly you hope it won=E2=80=
=99t. Probably=C2=A0you expect it won=E2=80=99t; commercial paper rarely de=
faults. Perhaps all of the commercial paper is highly rated and uncorrelate=
d to crypto; probably it will all mature at par. But asserting it=C2=A0<em>=
that=C2=A0</em>confidently =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cnone of our loans could =
possibly default=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0is not confidence-inspiring. Again=
, in the traditional financial system, banks simply do not go around saying=
 =E2=80=9Cnone of our investments could lose money=E2=80=9D and structuring=
 their balance sheets that way. Tether does!</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">It goes on:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Regarding the rec=
ent events impacting the Celsius lending platform, Celsius position has bee=
n liquidated with no losses to Tether. Tether=E2=80=99s lending activity wi=
th Celsius (as with any other borrower) has always been overcollateralized.=
 Tether has currently zero exposure to Celsius apart from a small investmen=
t made out of Tether equity in the company.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Tether is aware of other rumours being spread, suggesting that it has lend=
ing exposure to Three Arrows Capital - again this is categorically false.</=
p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fine, but, again, saying that y=
our crypto-backed loans have =E2=80=9Calways been overcollateralized=E2=80=
=9D is not <em>entirely=C2=A0</em>reassuring in a world where crypto prices=
 have fallen by two-thirds. Lots of stuff that was always overcollateralize=
d now isn=E2=80=99t. Similarly, =E2=80=9Cwe don=E2=80=99t lend to one hedge=
 fund that is rumored to be in trouble=E2=80=9D is not the same as =E2=80=
=9Cwe don=E2=80=99t lend to=C2=A0<em>any=C2=A0</em>hedge funds that are in =
trouble.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or there is <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28067458.269601/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uY29pbmRlc2suY29tL21hcmtldHMvMjAyMi8wNi8xMy90cm9ucy1zdGFibGVjb2luLXBlZy10by=
1kb2xsYXItd29iYmxlcy1qdXN0aW4tc3VuLXN3ZWFycy10by1kZXBsb3ktMmItdG8tcHJvcC11c=
C8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1ae8400b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">USDD</a>:</p><blockquote><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Tron network=E2=80=99s stablecoin, USDD, lost =
its peg to the U.S. dollar on Monday, dipping to as low as 91 cents, as cry=
pto markets nosedived as investors grew increasingly concerned about persis=
tently high inflation, tightening financial conditions and a potential rece=
ssion.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tron founder Justin Sun tweeted Mond=
ay that the funding rate on the Binance exchange for betting against, or "s=
horting," the Tron blockchain's native TRX token stood at negative 500%, a =
whopping rate that suggests many investors are clamoring to get into that t=
rade. According to Sun, TronDAO =E2=80=9Cwill deploy $2 billion to fight th=
em.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are two way=
s to think about USDD. One is that it is an algorithmic stablecoin like Ter=
raUSD, which <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28067=
458.269601/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjIt=
MDUtMTEvdGVycmEtZmxvcHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYxNTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1=
lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNjE1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj=
1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB86be760c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> collapsed hilari=
ously</a>=C2=A0<em>as USDD <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/28067458.269601/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMjMvdGhlLXNlYy1nb2VzLWFmdGVyLWdyZWVud2FzaGluZz9jbXBpZD1CQ=
kQwNjE1MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRl=
ciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA2MTUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cBfc52873c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> was launching</a></em>; pure algorithmic stablecoi=
ns are trivially vulnerable to death spirals if people lose confidence in t=
hem.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another way to think about USDD, thoug=
h, is that it is effectively a giant overcollateralized loan against Bitcoi=
n and TRX (and Tether, too). Like TerraUSD=E2=80=99s backers=C2=A0tried to =
do, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28067458.26960=
